 109: -- | Cl3 provides specialized constructors for sub-algebras and other geometric objects
 110: -- contained in the algebra.  Cl(3,0), abbreviated to Cl3, is a Geometric Algebra
 111: -- of 3 dimensional space known as the Algebra of Physical Space (APS).  Geometric Algebras are Real
 112: -- Clifford Algebras, double precision floats are used to approximate real numbers in this
 113: -- library.  Single and Double grade combinations are specialized using algebraic datatypes
 114: -- and live within the APS.
 115: --
 116: --   * 'R' is the constructor for the Real Scalar Sub-algebra Grade-0
 117: --
 118: --   * 'V3' is the Three Dimensional Real Vector constructor Grade-1
 119: --
 120: --   * 'BV' is the Bivector constructor Grade-2 an Imaginary Three Dimensional Vector
 121: --
 122: --   * 'I' is the Imaginary constructor Grade-3 and is the Pseudo-Scalar for APS
 123: --
 124: --   * 'PV' is the Paravector constructor with Grade-0 and Grade-1 elements, a Real Scalar plus Vector, (R + V3)
 125: --
 126: --   * 'H' is the Quaternion constructor it is the Even Sub-algebra with Grade-0 and Grade-2 elements, a Real Scalar plus Bivector, (R + BV)
 127: --
 128: --   * 'C' is the Complex constructor it is the Scalar Sub-algebra with Grade-0 and Grade-3 elements, a Real Scalar plus Imaginar Scalar, (R + I)
 129: --
 130: --   * 'BPV' is the Biparavector constructor with Grade-1 and Grade-2 elements, a Real Vector plus Bivector, (V3 + BV)
 131: --
 132: --   * 'ODD' is the Odd constructor with Grade-1 and Grade-3 elements, a Vector plus Imaginary Scalar, (V3 + I)
 133: --
 134: --   * 'TPV' is the Triparavector constructor with Grade-2 and Grade-3 elements, a Bivector plus Imaginary, (BV + I)
 135: --
 136: --   * 'APS' is the constructor for an element in the Algebra of Physical Space with Grade-0 through Grade-3 elements
 137: --
 138: data Cl3 where
 139:   R   :: !Double -> Cl3 -- Real Scalar Sub-algebra
 140:   V3  :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Three Dimensional Vectors
 141:   BV  :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Bivectors, Imaginary Three Dimenstional Vectors
 142:   I   :: !Double -> Cl3 -- Trivector Imaginary Pseudo-Scalar, Imaginary Scalar
 143:   PV  :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Paravector, Real Scalar plus Three Dimensional Real Vector, (R + V3)
 144:   H   :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Quaternion Even Sub-algebra, Real Scalar plus Bivector, (R + BV)
 145:   C   :: !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Complex Sub-algebra, Real Scalar plus Imaginary Scalar, (R + I)
 146:   BPV :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Biparavector, Vector plus Bivector, (V3 + BV)
 147:   ODD :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Odd, Vector plus Imaginary, (V3 + I)
 148:   TPV :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Triparavector, Bivector plus Imaginary Scalar, (BV + I)
 149:   APS :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3 -- Algebra of Physical Space
 150: #ifndef O_NO_DERIVED
 151:     deriving (Show, Read, Typeable, Data, Generic)
 152: 
 153: #else
 154: 
 155: -- | In case we don't derive Show, provide 'showOctave' as the Show instance
 156: instance Show Cl3 where
 157:   show = showOctave
 158: 
 159: #endif
 160: 
 161:

 348: 
 349: -- |Cl3 has a total preorder ordering in which all pairs are comparable by two real valued functions.
 350: -- Comparison of two reals is just the typical real compare function.  Comparison of to imaginary numbers
 351: -- is just the typical comparison function.  When reals are compared to anything else it will compare the
 352: -- absolute value of the reals to the magnitude of the other cliffor.  Compare of two complex values
 353: -- compares the polar magnitude of the complex numbers.  Compare of two vectors compares the vector
 354: -- magnitudes.  The Ord instance for the general case is based on the singular values of each cliffor and
 355: -- this Ordering compares the largest singular value 'abs' and then the littlest singular value 'lsv'.
 356: -- Some arbitrary cliffors may return EQ for Ord but not be exactly '==' equivalent, but they are related
 357: -- by a right and left multiplication of two unitary elements.  For instance for the Cliffors A and B,
 358: -- A == B could be False, but compare A B is EQ, because A * V = U * B, where V and U are unitary.  
 359: instance Ord Cl3 where
 360:   compare (R a0) (R b0) = compare a0 b0 -- Real Numbers have a total order within the limitations of Double Precision comparison
 361:   compare (I a123) (I b123) = compare a123 b123 -- Imaginary Numbers have a total order within the limitations of Double Precision comparison
 362:   compare cliffor1 cliffor2 =
 363:      let (R a0) = abs cliffor1
 364:          (R b0) = abs cliffor2
 365:          (R a0') = lsv cliffor1
 366:          (R b0') = lsv cliffor2
 367:      in case compare a0 b0 of
 368:           LT -> LT
 369:           GT -> GT
 370:           EQ -> compare a0' b0'
 371: 
 372: 
 373: 
 374: -- |Cl3 has a "Num" instance.  "Num" is addition, geometric product, negation, 'abs' the largest
 375: -- singular value, and 'signum'.
 376: -- 
 377: instance Num Cl3 where
 378:   -- | Cl3 can be added
 379:   (R a0) + (R b0) = R (a0 + b0)
 380: 
 381:   (R a0) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = PV a0 b1 b2 b3
 382:   (R a0) + (BV b23 b31 b12) = H a0 b23 b31 b12
 383:   (R a0) + (I b123) = C a0 b123
 384:   (R a0) + (PV b0 b1 b2 b3) = PV (a0 + b0) b1 b2 b3
 385:   (R a0) + (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = H (a0 + b0) b23 b31 b12
 386:   (R a0) + (C b0 b123) = C (a0 + b0) b123
 387:   (R a0) + (BPV b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12) = APS a0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 0
 388:   (R a0) + (ODD b1 b2 b3 b123) = APS a0 b1 b2 b3 0 0 0 b123
 389:   (R a0) + (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS a0 0 0 0 b23 b31 b12 b123
 390:   (R a0) + (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (a0 + b0) b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123
 391: 
 392:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (R b0) = PV b0 a1 a2 a3
 393:   (BV a23 a31 a12) + (R b0) = H b0 a23 a31 a12
 394:   (I a123) + (R b0) = C b0 a123
 395:   (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) + (R b0) = PV (a0 + b0) a1 a2 a3
 396:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) + (R b0) = H (a0 + b0) a23 a31 a12
 397:   (C a0 a123) + (R b0) = C (a0 + b0) a123
 398:   (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) + (R b0) = APS b0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 0
 399:   (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) + (R b0) = APS b0 a1 a2 a3 0 0 0 a123
 400:   (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) + (R b0) = APS b0 0 0 0 a23 a31 a12 a123
 401:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) + (R b0) = APS (a0 + b0) a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123
 402: 
 403:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = V3 (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3)

 405:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (BV b23 b31 b12) = BPV a1 a2 a3 b23 b31 b12

 407:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (PV b0 b1 b2 b3) = PV b0 (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3)
 408:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = APS b0 a1 a2 a3 b23 b31 b12 0
 409:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (C b0 b123) = APS b0 a1 a2 a3 0 0 0 b123
 410:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (BPV b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12) = BPV (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3) b23 b31 b12
 411:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (ODD b1 b2 b3 b123) = ODD (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3) b123
 412:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS 0 a1 a2 a3 b23 b31 b12 b123
 413:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) + (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS b0 (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3) b23 b31 b12 b123
 414: 
 415:   (BV a23 a31 a12) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = BPV b1 b2 b3 a23 a31 a12
 416:   (I a123) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = ODD b1 b2 b3 a123

 418:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = APS a0 b1 b2 b3 a23 a31 a12 0
 419:   (C a0 a123) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = APS a0 b1 b2 b3 0 0 0 a123
 420:   (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = BPV (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3) a23 a31 a12
 421:   (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) + (V3 b1 b2 b3) = ODD (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3) a123

 436:   (I a123) + (BV b23 b31 b12) = TPV b23 b31 b12 a123

 528: 
 529:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) + (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (a0 + b0)
 530:                                                                                 (a1 + b1) (a2 + b2) (a3 + b3)

 532:                                                                                 (a123 + b123)
 533: 
 534:   -- | Multiplication Instance implementing a Geometric Product
 535:   (R a0) * (R b0) = R (a0*b0)
 536: 
 537:   (R a0) * (V3 b1 b2 b3) = V3 (a0*b1) (a0*b2) (a0*b3)
 538:   (R a0) * (BV b23 b31 b12) = BV (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 539:   (R a0) * (I b123) = I (a0*b123)
 540:   (R a0) * (PV b0 b1 b2 b3) = PV (a0*b0)
 541:                                  (a0*b1) (a0*b2) (a0*b3)
 542:   (R a0) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = H (a0*b0)
 543:                                   (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 544:   (R a0) * (C b0 b123) = C (a0*b0)
 545:                            (a0*b123)
 546:   (R a0) * (BPV b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12) = BPV (a0*b1) (a0*b2) (a0*b3)
 547:                                             (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 548:   (R a0) * (ODD b1 b2 b3 b123) = ODD (a0*b1) (a0*b2) (a0*b3)
 549:                                      (a0*b123)
 550:   (R a0) * (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = TPV (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 551:                                         (a0*b123)
 552:   (R a0) * (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (a0*b0)
 553:                                                     (a0*b1) (a0*b2) (a0*b3)
 554:                                                     (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 555:                                                     (a0*b123)
 556: 
 557:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) * (R b0) = V3 (a1*b0) (a2*b0) (a3*b0)
 558:   (BV a23 a31 a12) * (R b0) = BV (a23*b0) (a31*b0) (a12*b0)
 559:   (I a123) * (R b0) = I (a123*b0)
 560:   (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) * (R b0) = PV (a0*b0)
 561:                                  (a1*b0) (a2*b0) (a3*b0)
 562:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) * (R b0) = H (a0*b0)
 563:                                   (a23*b0) (a31*b0) (a12*b0)
 564:   (C a0 a123) * (R b0) = C (a0*b0)
 565:                            (a123*b0)
 566:   (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) * (R b0) = BPV (a1*b0) (a2*b0) (a3*b0)
 567:                                             (a23*b0) (a31*b0) (a12*b0)
 568:   (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) * (R b0) = ODD (a1*b0) (a2*b0) (a3*b0)
 569:                                      (a123*b0)
 570:   (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) * (R b0) = TPV (a23*b0) (a31*b0) (a12*b0)
 571:                                         (a123*b0)
 572:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) * (R b0) = APS (a0*b0)
 573:                                                     (a1*b0) (a2*b0) (a3*b0)
 574:                                                     (a23*b0) (a31*b0) (a12*b0)
 575:                                                     (a123*b0)
 576: 
 577:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) * (V3 b1 b2 b3) = H (a1*b1 + a2*b2 + a3*b3)
 578:                                     (a2*b3 - a3*b2) (a3*b1 - a1*b3) (a1*b2 - a2*b1)
 579: 
 580:   (V3 a1 a2 a3) * (BV b23 b31 b12) = ODD (a3*b31 - a2*b12) (a1*b12 - a3*b23) (a2*b23 - a1*b31)

 798:                                                         (a0*b23 - a31*b12 + a12*b31) (a0*b31 + a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a0*b12 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 799:                                                         (a23*b1 + a31*b2  + a12*b3)
 800:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) * (ODD b1 b2 b3 b123) = ODD (a0*b1 + a12*b2 - a31*b3 - a23*b123)
 801:                                                  (a0*b2 - a12*b1 + a23*b3 - a31*b123)
 802:                                                  (a0*b3 + a31*b1 - a23*b2 - a12*b123)
 803:                                                  (a0*b123 + a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)
 804:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) * (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12)
 805:                                                     (negate $ a23*b123) (negate $ a31*b123) (negate $ a12*b123)
 806:                                                     (a0*b23 - a31*b12 + a12*b31) (a0*b31 + a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a0*b12 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 807:                                                     (a0*b123)
 808:   (H a0 a23 a31 a12) * (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (a0*b0 - a23*b23 - a31*b31 - a12*b12)
 809:                                                                 (a0*b1 + a12*b2 - a31*b3 - a23*b123)
 810:                                                                 (a0*b2 - a12*b1 + a23*b3 - a31*b123)
 811:                                                                 (a0*b3 + a31*b1 - a23*b2 - a12*b123)
 812:                                                                 (a0*b23 + a23*b0 - a31*b12 + a12*b31)
 813:                                                                 (a0*b31 + a31*b0 + a23*b12 - a12*b23)
 814:                                                                 (a0*b12 + a12*b0 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 815:                                                                 (a0*b123 + a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)
 816: 
 817:   (C a0 a123) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = APS (a0*b0)
 818:                                          (negate $ a123*b23) (negate $ a123*b31) (negate $ a123*b12)
 819:                                          (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 820:                                          (a123*b0)
 821:   (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12)
 822:                                                         (a1*b0 - a2*b12 + a3*b31) (a2*b0 + a1*b12 - a3*b23) (a3*b0 - a1*b31 + a2*b23)
 823:                                                         (a23*b0 - a31*b12 + a12*b31) (a31*b0 + a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a12*b0 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 824:                                                         (a1*b23 + a2*b31 + a3*b12)
 825:   (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = ODD (a1*b0 - a2*b12 + a3*b31 - a123*b23)
 826:                                                  (a2*b0 + a1*b12 - a3*b23 - a123*b31)
 827:                                                  (a3*b0 - a1*b31 + a2*b23 - a123*b12)
 828:                                                  (a123*b0 + a1*b23 + a2*b31 + a3*b12)
 829:   (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12)
 830:                                                     (negate $ a123*b23) (negate $ a123*b31) (negate $ a123*b12)
 831:                                                     (a23*b0 - a31*b12 + a12*b31) (a31*b0 + a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a12*b0 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 832:                                                     (a123*b0)
 833:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) * (H b0 b23 b31 b12) = APS (a0*b0 - a23*b23 - a31*b31 - a12*b12)
 834:                                                                 (a1*b0 - a2*b12 + a3*b31 - a123*b23)
 835:                                                                 (a2*b0 + a1*b12 - a3*b23 - a123*b31)
 836:                                                                 (a3*b0 - a1*b31 + a2*b23 - a123*b12)
 837:                                                                 (a0*b23 + a23*b0 - a31*b12 + a12*b31)
 838:                                                                 (a0*b31 + a31*b0 + a23*b12 - a12*b23)
 839:                                                                 (a0*b12 + a12*b0 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 840:                                                                 (a123*b0 + a1*b23 + a2*b31 + a3*b12)
 841: 
 842:   (C a0 a123) * (C b0 b123) = C (a0*b0 - a123*b123)
 843:                                 (a0*b123 + a123*b0)
 844:

 846:                                                  (a0*b23 + a123*b1) (a0*b31 + a123*b2) (a0*b12 + a123*b3)

 853:                                              (a0*b23) (a0*b31) (a0*b12)
 854:                                              (a0*b123)

 876:                                                                 (a12*b2 - a2*b12 + a3*b31 - a31*b3)

 906:                                                             (a12*b2 - a31*b3 - a123*b23) (a23*b3 - a12*b1 - a123*b31) (a31*b1 - a23*b2 - a123*b12)
 907:                                                             (a123*b1 - a31*b12 + a12*b31) (a123*b2 + a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a123*b3 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 908:                                                             (a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)

 910:                                                                         (a0*b1 - a2*b12 + a12*b2 + a3*b31 - a31*b3 - a123*b23)

 916:                                                                         (a1*b23 + a23*b1 + a2*b31 + a31*b2 + a3*b12 + a12*b3)

 924:                                                      (a3*b31 - a2*b12 - a123*b23) (a1*b12 - a3*b23 - a123*b31) (a2*b23 - a1*b31 - a123*b12)
 925:                                                      (a1*b123) (a2*b123) (a3*b123)
 926:                                                      (a1*b23 + a2*b31 + a3*b12)
 927:   (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) * (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (a1*b1 + a2*b2 + a3*b3 - a123*b123)
 928:                                                                  (a1*b0 - a2*b12 + a3*b31 - a123*b23)
 929:                                                                  (a2*b0 + a1*b12 - a3*b23 - a123*b31)
 930:                                                                  (a3*b0 - a1*b31 + a2*b23 - a123*b12)
 931:                                                                  (a1*b123 + a123*b1 + a2*b3 - a3*b2)

 938:                                                      (a123*b1) (a123*b2) (a123*b3)
 939:                                                      (a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)
 940:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) * (ODD b1 b2 b3 b123) = APS (a1*b1 + a2*b2 + a3*b3 - a123*b123)
 941:                                                                  (a0*b1 + a12*b2 - a31*b3 - a23*b123)
 942:                                                                  (a0*b2 - a12*b1 + a23*b3 - a31*b123)
 943:                                                                  (a0*b3 + a31*b1 - a23*b2 - a12*b123)
 944:                                                                  (a1*b123 + a123*b1 + a2*b3 - a3*b2)
 945:                                                                  (a2*b123 + a123*b2 - a1*b3 + a3*b1)
 946:                                                                  (a3*b123 + a123*b3 + a1*b2 - a2*b1)
 947:                                                                  (a0*b123 + a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)
 948: 
 949:   (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) * (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12 + a123*b123)
 950:                                                         (negate $ a23*b123 + a123*b23) (negate $ a31*b123 + a123*b31) (negate $ a12*b123 + a123*b12)
 951:                                                         (a12*b31 - a31*b12) (a23*b12 - a12*b23) (a31*b23 - a23*b31)
 952:                                                         0
 953: 
 954:   (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) * (APS b0 b1 b2 b3 b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12 + a123*b123)
 955:                                                                     (a12*b2 - a31*b3 - a23*b123 - a123*b23)
 956:                                                                     (a23*b3 - a12*b1 - a31*b123 - a123*b31)
 957:                                                                     (a31*b1 - a23*b2 - a12*b123 - a123*b12)
 958:                                                                     (a23*b0 + a123*b1 - a31*b12 + a12*b31)
 959:                                                                     (a31*b0 + a123*b2 + a23*b12 - a12*b23)
 960:                                                                     (a12*b0 + a123*b3 - a23*b31 + a31*b23)
 961:                                                                     (a123*b0 + a23*b1 + a31*b2 + a12*b3)
 962: 
 963:   (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) * (TPV b23 b31 b12 b123) = APS (negate $ a23*b23 + a31*b31 + a12*b12 + a123*b123)
 964:                                                                     (a3*b31 - a2*b12 - a23*b123 - a123*b23)
 965:                                                                     (a1*b12 - a3*b23 - a31*b123 - a123*b31)
 966:                                                                     (a2*b23 - a1*b31 - a12*b123 - a123*b12)

 973:                                                                                 (a0*b1 + a1*b0 - a2*b12 + a12*b2 + a3*b31 - a31*b3 - a23*b123 - a123*b23)
 974:                                                                                 (a0*b2 + a2*b0 + a1*b12 - a12*b1 - a3*b23 + a23*b3 - a31*b123 - a123*b31)

 979:                                                                                 (a0*b123 + a123*b0 + a1*b23 + a23*b1 + a2*b31 + a31*b2 + a3*b12 + a12*b3)

 983: 
 984:   -- |'abs' is the spectral norm aka the spectral radius
 985:   -- it is the largest singular value. This function may need to be fiddled with
 986:   -- to make the math a bit safer wrt overflows.  This makes use of the largest
 987:   -- singular value, if the littlest singular value is zero then the element is not
 988:   -- invertable, we can see here that R, C, V3, BV, and H are all invertable, and
 989:   -- by implication R, C, and H are division algebras.
 990:   abs cl3 = fst $ abssignum cl3
 991:   {-
  abs (R a0) = R (abs a0) -- absolute value of a real number
  abs (V3 a1 a2 a3) = R (sqrt $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2) -- magnitude of a vector
  abs (BV a23 a31 a12) = R (sqrt $ a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2) -- magnitude of a bivector
  abs (I a123) = R (abs a123) -- magnitude of a Imaginary number
  abs (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) = R (reimMag a0 a1 a2 a3)
  abs (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) = R (reimMag a123 a23 a31 a12)
  abs (H a0 a23 a31 a12) = R (sqrt $ a0^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2) -- largest singular value
  abs (C a0 a123) = R (sqrt $ a0^2 + a123^2) -- magnitude of a complex number
  abs (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) =
    let mag = sqrt $ (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 + (a1*a12 - a3*a23)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 -- core was duplicating this computation added let to hopefully reduce the duplication
    in R (sqrt $ a1^2 + a23^2 + a2^2 + mag + a31^2 + a3^2 + a12^2 + mag)
  abs (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) = R (sqrt $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a123^2)
  abs (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) =
    let mag = sqrt $ (a0*a1 + a123*a23)^2 + (a0*a2 + a123*a31)^2 + (a0*a3 + a123*a12)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 + (a3*a23 - a1*a12)^2 + (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 -- core was duplicating this computation added let to hopefully reduce the duplication
    in R (sqrt $ a0^2 + a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + mag + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 + a123^2 + mag)
  -}
1008: 
1009:   -- |'signum' satisfies the Law "abs x * signum x == x"
1010:   -- kind of cool: signum of a vector is it's unit vector.
1011:   signum cl3 = snd $ abssignum cl3
1012:   {-
  signum (R a0) = R (signum a0)
  signum (V3 a1 a2 a3) =
    let mag = sqrt (a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else V3 (invMag * a1) (invMag * a2) (invMag * a3)
  signum (BV a23 a31 a12) =
    let mag = sqrt (a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else BV (invMag * a23) (invMag * a31) (invMag * a12)
  signum (I a123) =
    if a123 == 0
    then R 0
    else I (signum a123)
  signum (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) =
    let mag = reimMag a0 a1 a2 a3
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else PV (invMag * a0) (invMag * a1) (invMag * a2) (invMag * a3)
  signum (H a0 a23 a31 a12) =
    let mag = sqrt (a0^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else H (invMag * a0) (invMag * a23) (invMag * a31) (invMag * a12)
  signum (C a0 a123) =
    let mag = sqrt (a0^2 + a123^2)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else C (invMag * a0) (invMag * a123)
  signum (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) =
    let x = sqrt ((a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 + (a1*a12 - a3*a23)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2)
        mag = sqrt (a1^2 + a23^2 + a2^2 + a31^2 + a3^2 + a12^2 + x + x)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else BPV (invMag * a1) (invMag * a2) (invMag * a3) (invMag * a23) (invMag * a31) (invMag * a12)
  signum (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) =
    let mag = sqrt (a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a123^2)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else ODD (invMag * a1) (invMag * a2) (invMag * a3) (invMag * a123)
  signum (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) =
    let mag = reimMag a123 a23 a31 a12
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else TPV (invMag * a23) (invMag * a31) (invMag * a12) (invMag * a123)
  signum (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) =
    let x = sqrt ((a0*a1 + a123*a23)^2 + (a0*a2 + a123*a31)^2 + (a0*a3 + a123*a12)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 + (a3*a23 - a1*a12)^2 + (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2)
        mag = sqrt (a0^2 + a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 + a123^2 + x + x)
        invMag = recip mag
    in if mag == 0
       then R 0
       else APS (invMag * a0) (invMag * a1) (invMag * a2) (invMag * a3) (invMag * a23) (invMag * a31) (invMag * a12) (invMag * a123)
  -}

1109: -- |Cl(3,0) has a Fractional instance
1110: instance Fractional Cl3 where
1111:   -- |Some of the sub algebras are division algebras but APS is not a division algebra
1112:   recip (R a0) = R (recip a0)   -- R is a division algebra
1113:   recip cliff = 
1114:     let (R mag) = abs cliff
1115:         recipsqmag = recip mag^2
1116:         negrecipsqmag = negate recipsqmag
1117:         recipmag2 = recip.toR $ cliff * bar cliff
1118:         go_recip (V3 a1 a2 a3) = V3 (recipsqmag * a1) (recipsqmag * a2) (recipsqmag * a3)
1119:         go_recip (BV a23 a31 a12) = BV (negrecipsqmag * a23) (negrecipsqmag * a31) (negrecipsqmag * a12)
1120:         go_recip (I a123) = I (negrecipsqmag * a123)
1121:         go_recip (H a0 a23 a31 a12) = H (recipsqmag * a0) (negrecipsqmag * a23) (negrecipsqmag * a31) (negrecipsqmag * a12)  -- H is a division algebra
1122:         go_recip (C a0 a123) = C (recipsqmag * a0) (negrecipsqmag * a123)   -- C is a division algebra
1123:         go_recip (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) = ODD (recipsqmag * a1) (recipsqmag * a2) (recipsqmag * a3) (negrecipsqmag * a123)
1124:         go_recip pv@PV{} = recipmag2 * bar pv
1125:         go_recip tpv@TPV{} = recipmag2 * bar tpv
1126:         go_recip cliffor = reduce $ spectraldcmp recip recip' cliffor
1127:     in go_recip cliff

1632: -- |'lsv' the littlest singular value. Useful for testing for invertability.
1633: lsv :: Cl3 -> Cl3
1634: lsv (R a0) = R (abs a0) -- absolute value of a real number
1635: lsv (V3 a1 a2 a3) = R (sqrt (a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2)) -- magnitude of a vector
1636: lsv (BV a23 a31 a12) = R (sqrt (a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2)) -- magnitude of a bivector
1637: lsv (I a123) = R (abs a123)
1638: lsv (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) = R (loDisc a0 a1 a2 a3)
1639: lsv (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) = R (loDisc a123 a23 a31 a12)
1640: lsv (H a0 a23 a31 a12) = R (sqrt (a0^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2))
1641: lsv (C a0 a123) = R (sqrt (a0^2 + a123^2)) -- magnitude of a complex number
1642: lsv (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) =
1643:   let x = negate.sqrt $ (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 + (a1*a12 - a3*a23)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 -- core was duplicating this computation added let to hopefully reduce the duplication
1644:       y = a1^2 + a23^2 + a2^2 + x + a31^2 + a3^2 + a12^2 + x -- attempted to balance out the sum of several positives with a negitive before the next sum of positives and negitive
1645:   in if y <= tol' -- gaurd for numerical errors, y could be negative with large enough biparavectors
1646:      then R 0
1647:      else R (sqrt y)
1648: lsv (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) = R (sqrt (a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a123^2))
1649: lsv (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) =
1650:   let x = negate.sqrt $ (a0*a1 + a123*a23)^2 + (a0*a2 + a123*a31)^2 + (a0*a3 + a123*a12)^2 +
1651:                         (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 + (a3*a23 - a1*a12)^2 + (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 -- core was duplicating this computation added let to hopefully reduce the duplication
1652:       y = a0^2 + a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + x + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 + a123^2 + x -- attempted to balance out the sum of several positives with a negitive before the next sum of positives and negitive
1653:   in if y <= tol' -- gaurd for numerical errors, y could be negative with large enough cliffors
1654:      then R 0
1655:      else R (sqrt y)
1656:

1668: 
1669: -- | 'spectraldcmp' the spectral decomposition of a function to calculate analytic functions of cliffors in Cl(3,0).
1670: -- This function requires the desired function's R, I, and C instances to be calculated and the function's derivative.
1671: -- If multiple functions are being composed, its best to pass the composition of the funcitons
1672: -- to this function and the derivative to this function.  Any function with a Taylor Series
1673: -- approximation should be able to be used.  A real, imaginary, and complex version of the function to be decomposed
1674: -- must be provided and spectraldcmp will handle the case for an arbitrary Cliffor.
1675: -- 
1676: -- It may be possible to add, in the future, a RULES pragma like:
1677: --
1678: -- > "spectral decomposition function composition"
1679: -- > forall f f' g g' cliff.
1680: -- > spectraldcmp f f' (spectraldcmp g g' cliff) = spectraldcmp (f.g) (f'.g') cliff
1681: -- 
1682: -- 
1683: spectraldcmp :: (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> Cl3 -> Cl3
1684: spectraldcmp fun fun' (reduce -> cliffor) = dcmp cliffor
1685:   where
1686:     dcmp r@R{} = fun r
1687:     dcmp i@I{} = fun i
1688:     dcmp c@C{} = fun c
1689:     dcmp v@V3{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toR fun v -- spectprojR fun v
1690:     dcmp pv@PV{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toR fun pv -- spectprojR fun pv
1691:     dcmp bv@BV{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toI fun bv -- spectprojI fun bv
1692:     dcmp tpv@TPV{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toI fun tpv -- spectprojI fun tpv
1693:     dcmp h@H{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toC fun h -- spectprojC fun h
1694:     dcmp od@ODD{} = spectraldcmpSpecial toC fun od -- spectprojC fun od
1695:     dcmp cliff
1696:       | hasNilpotent cliff = jordan toC fun fun' cliff  -- jordan normal form Cl3 style
1697:       | isColinear cliff = spectraldcmpSpecial toC fun cliff -- spectprojC fun bpv
1698:       | otherwise =                               -- transform it so it will be colinear
1699:           let (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) = toBPV cliff
1700:               boost = boost2colinear a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12
1701:           in boost * spectraldcmpSpecial toC fun (bar boost * cliff * boost) * bar boost -- v * spectprojC fun d * v_bar
1702: --
1703: 
1704: 
1705: -- | 'jordan' does a Cl(3,0) version of the decomposition into Jordan Normal Form and Matrix Function Calculation
1706: -- The intended use is for calculating functions for cliffors with vector parts simular to Nilpotent.
1707: -- It is a helper function for 'spectraldcmp'.  It is fortunate because eigen decomposition doesn't
1708: -- work with elements with nilpotent content, so it fills the gap.
1709: jordan :: (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> Cl3 -> Cl3
1710: jordan toSpecial fun fun' cliffor =
1711:   let eigs = toSpecial cliffor
1712:   in fun eigs + fun' eigs * toBPV cliffor
1713: 
1714: -- | 'spectraldcmpSpecial' helper function for with specialization for real, imaginary, or complex eigenvalues.
1715: -- To specialize for Reals pass 'toR', to specialize for Imaginary pass 'toI', to specialize for Complex pass 'toC'
1716: spectraldcmpSpecial :: (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> Cl3 -> Cl3
1717: spectraldcmpSpecial toSpecial function cliffor =
1718:   let (p,p_bar,eig1,eig2) = projEigs toSpecial cliffor
1719:   in function eig1 * p + function eig2 * p_bar
1720:

1758: -- | 'project' makes a projector based off of the vector content of the Cliffor.
1759: project :: Cl3 -> Cl3  -- PV<:Cl3
1760: project R{} = PV 0.5 0 0 0.5   -- default to e3 direction
1761: project I{} = PV 0.5 0 0 0.5   -- default to e3 direction
1762: project C{} = PV 0.5 0 0 0.5   -- default to e3 direction
1763: project (V3 a1 a2 a3) = triDProj a1 a2 a3   -- proj v@V3{} = 0.5 + 0.5*signum v
1764: project (PV _ a1 a2 a3) = triDProj a1 a2 a3   -- proj pv@PV{} = 0.5 + 0.5*(signum.toV3 $ pv)
1765: project (ODD a1 a2 a3 _) = triDProj a1 a2 a3   -- od@ODD{} = 0.5 + 0.5*(signum.toV3 $ od)
1766: project (BV a23 a31 a12) = triDProj a23 a31 a12   -- bv@BV{} = 0.5 + 0.5*(mIx.signum $ bv)
1767: project (H _ a23 a31 a12) = triDProj a23 a31 a12   -- h@H{} = 0.5 + 0.5*(mIx.signum.toBV $ h)
1768: project (TPV a23 a31 a12 _) = triDProj a23 a31 a12   -- tpv@TPV{} = 0.5 + 0.5*(mIx.signum.toBV $ tpv)
1769: project (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) = biTriDProj a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12
1770: project (APS _ a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 _) = biTriDProj a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12
1771: 
1772: 
1773: 
1774: -- If Dot product is negative or zero we have a problem, if it is zero
1775: -- it either the vector or bivector par is zero or they are orthognal
1776: -- if the dot product is negative the vectors could be antiparallel

1810: 
1811: -- | 'boost2colinear' calculates a boost that is perpendicular to both the vector and bivector
1812: -- components of the cliffor, that will mix the vector and bivector parts such that the vector and bivector
1813: -- parts become colinear. This function is a simularity transform such that:
1814: --
1815: -- > cliffor = boost * colinear * bar boost
1816: --
1817: -- and returns the boost given the inputs.  First the boost must be calculated
1818: -- and then
1819: --
1820: -- > colinear = bar boost * cliffor * boost
1821: --
1822: -- and colinear will have colinear vector and bivector parts of the cliffor.
1823: -- This is somewhat simular to finding the drift frame for a static electromagnetic field.
1824: --
1825: -- > v = toV3 cliffor  -- extract the vector
1826: -- > bv = mIx.toBV $ cliffor  -- extract the bivector and turn it into a vector
1827: -- > invariant = ((2*).mIx.toBV $ v * bv) / (toR (v^2) + toR (bv^2))
1828: -- > boost = spectraldcmpSpecial toR (exp.(/4).atanh) invariant
1829: --
1830: boost2colinear :: Double -> Double -> Double -> Double -> Double -> Double -> Cl3  -- PV<:Cl3
1831: boost2colinear a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 =
1832:   let scale = recip $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2
1833:       b1 = scale * (a2*a12 - a3*a31)
1834:       b2 = scale * (a3*a23 - a1*a12)
1835:       b3 = scale * (a1*a31 - a2*a23)
1836:       eig1 = (2*).sqrt $ b1^2 + b2^2 + b3^2
1837:       eig2 = negate eig1
1838:       transEig1 = exp.(/4).atanh $ eig1
1839:       transEig2 = exp.(/4).atanh $ eig2
1840:       sumTransEigs = (transEig1 - transEig2) * recip eig1
1841:   in PV (0.5 * (transEig1 + transEig2)) (sumTransEigs * b1) (sumTransEigs * b2) (sumTransEigs * b3)
1842: 
1843: 
1844: -- | 'isColinear' takes a Cliffor and determines if either the vector part or the bivector part are
1845: -- zero or both aligned in the same direction.
1846: isColinear :: Cl3 -> Bool
1847: isColinear R{} = True
1848: isColinear V3{} = True
1849: isColinear BV{} = True
1850: isColinear I{} = True
1851: isColinear PV{} = True
1852: isColinear H{} = True
1853: isColinear C{} = True
1854: isColinear ODD{} = True
1855: isColinear TPV{} = True
1856: isColinear (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) = colinearHelper a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12
1857: isColinear (APS _ a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 _) = colinearHelper a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12

1917: 
1918: -- | 'projEigs' function returns complementary projectors and eigenvalues for a Cliffor with specialization.
1919: -- The Cliffor at this point is allready colinear and the Eigenvalue is known to be real, imaginary, or complex.
1920: projEigs :: (Cl3 -> Cl3) -> Cl3 -> (Cl3,Cl3,Cl3,Cl3)
1921: projEigs toSpecial cliffor =
1922:   let p = project cliffor
1923:       p_bar = bar p
1924:       eig1 = 2 * toSpecial (p * cliffor * p)
1925:       eig2 = 2 * toSpecial (p_bar * cliffor * p_bar)
1926:   in (p,p_bar,eig1,eig2)
1927: 
1928: -- | 'reduce' function reduces the number of grades in a specialized Cliffor if they
1929: -- are zero-ish
1930: reduce :: Cl3 -> Cl3
1931: reduce cliff
1932:   | abs cliff <= tol = R 0
1933:   | otherwise = go_reduce cliff
1934:     where
1935:       go_reduce r@R{} = r
1936:       go_reduce v@V3{} = v
1937:       go_reduce bv@BV{} = bv
1938:       go_reduce i@I{} = i
1939:       go_reduce pv@PV{}
1940:         | abs (toV3 pv) <= tol = toR pv
1941:         | abs (toR pv) <= tol = toV3 pv
1942:         | otherwise = pv
1943:       go_reduce h@H{}
1944:         | abs (toBV h) <= tol = toR h
1945:         | abs (toR h) <= tol = toBV h
1946:         | otherwise = h
1947:       go_reduce c@C{}
1948:         | abs (toI c) <= tol = toR c
1949:         | abs (toR c) <= tol = toI c
1950:         | otherwise = c
1951:       go_reduce bpv@BPV{}
1952:         | abs (toBV bpv) <= tol = toV3 bpv
1953:         | abs (toV3 bpv) <= tol = toBV bpv
1954:         | otherwise = bpv
1955:       go_reduce od@ODD{}
1956:         | abs (toI od) <= tol = toV3 od
1957:         | abs (toV3 od) <= tol = toI od
1958:         | otherwise = od
1959:       go_reduce tpv@TPV{}
1960:         | abs (toBV tpv) <= tol = toI tpv
1961:         | abs (toI tpv) <= tol = toBV tpv
1962:         | otherwise = tpv
1963:       go_reduce aps@APS{}
1964:         | abs (toBPV aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toC aps)
1965:         | abs (toODD aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toH aps)
1966:         | abs (toTPV aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toPV aps)
1967:         | abs (toC aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toBPV aps)
1968:         | abs (toH aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toODD aps)
1969:         | abs (toPV aps) <= tol = go_reduce (toTPV aps)
1970:         | otherwise = aps
1971:

2003: -- | 'abssignum' is a more effecient '\cl3 -> (abs cl3, signum cl3)'
2004: -- So 'abs' is always R and 'signum' is the same type of constructor as the input
2005: -- 'signum' is the element divided by its largest singular value 'abs'
2006: {-
abssignum :: Cl3 -> (Cl3,Cl3)
abssignum (R a0) = (R (abs a0),R (signum a0))
abssignum (V3 a1 a2 a3) = let mag = sqrt $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 in ((R mag),V3 (a1/mag) (a2/mag) (a3/mag))
abssignum (BV a23 a31 a12) = let mag = sqrt $ a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 in ((R mag),BV (a23/mag) (a31/mag) (a12/mag))
abssignum (I a123) = (R (abs a123),I (signum a123))
abssignum (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) = let mag = reimMag a0 a1 a2 a3 in (R (mag),PV (a0/mag) (a1/mag) (a2/mag) (a3/mag))
abssignum (H a0 a23 a31 a12) = let mag = sqrt $ a0^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 in ((R mag),H (a0/mag) (a23/mag) (a31/mag) (a12/mag))
abssignum (C a0 a123) = let mag = sqrt $ a0^2 + a123^2 in ((R mag),C (a0/mag) (a123/mag))
abssignum (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) =
  let mag0 = sqrt $ (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 + (a1*a12 - a3*a23)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2
      mag = sqrt $ a1^2 + a23^2 + a2^2 + mag0 + a31^2 + a3^2 + a12^2 + mag0 
  in (R (mag),BPV (a1/mag) (a2/mag) (a3/mag) (a23/mag) (a31/mag) (a12/mag))
abssignum (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) = let mag = sqrt $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a123^2 in (R (mag),ODD (a1/mag) (a2/mag) (a3/mag) (a123/mag))
abssignum (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) = let mag = reimMag a123 a23 a31 a12 in (R (mag),TPV (a23/mag) (a31/mag) (a12/mag) (a123/mag))
abssignum (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) =
  let mag0 = sqrt $ (a0*a1 + a123*a23)^2 + (a0*a2 + a123*a31)^2 + (a0*a3 + a123*a12)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 + (a3*a23 - a1*a12)^2 + (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2
      mag = sqrt $ a0^2 + a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + mag0 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 + a123^2 + mag0
  in (R (mag), APS (a0/mag) (a1/mag) (a2/mag) (a3/mag) (a23/mag) (a31/mag) (a12/mag) (a123/mag))
-}
2026: abssignum :: Cl3 -> (Cl3,Cl3)
2027: abssignum cl3 =
2028:   let (R m0) = absolute cl3
2029:   in if m0 == 0
2030:      then (R 0, R 0) -- (abs 0 == 0, signum 0 == 0)
2031:      else (R m0, cl3/(R m0))

2065: -- | 'bar' is a Clifford Conjugate, the vector grades are negated
2066: bar :: Cl3 -> Cl3
2067: bar (R a0) = R a0
2068: bar (V3 a1 a2 a3) = V3 (negate a1) (negate a2) (negate a3)
2069: bar (BV a23 a31 a12) = BV (negate a23) (negate a31) (negate a12)
2070: bar (I a123) = I a123
2071: bar (PV a0 a1 a2 a3) = PV a0 (negate a1) (negate a2) (negate a3)
2072: bar (H a0 a23 a31 a12) = H a0 (negate a23) (negate a31) (negate a12)
2073: bar (C a0 a123) = C a0 a123
2074: bar (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12) = BPV (negate a1) (negate a2) (negate a3) (negate a23) (negate a31) (negate a12)
2075: bar (ODD a1 a2 a3 a123) = ODD (negate a1) (negate a2) (negate a3) a123
2076: bar (TPV a23 a31 a12 a123) = TPV (negate a23) (negate a31) (negate a12) a123
2077: bar (APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) = APS a0 (negate a1) (negate a2) (negate a3) (negate a23) (negate a31) (negate a12) a123

2300: #ifndef O_NO_STORABLE
2301: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2302: -- 
2303: -- Instance of Cl3 types with the "Foreign.Storable" library.
2304: --  
2305: -- For use with high performance data structures like Data.Vector.Storable
2306: -- or Data.Array.Storable
2307: -- 
2308: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2309: 
2310: -- | Cl3 instance of Storable uses the APS constructor as its standard interface.
2311: -- "peek" returns a cliffor constructed with APS. "poke" converts a cliffor to APS.
2312: -- For a more compact storing of constructors other than APS use the storable
2313: -- subtypes Cl3_R, Cl3_V3, Cl3_BV, Cl3_I, Cl3_PV, Cl3_H, Cl3_C, Cl3_BPV,
2314: -- Cl3_ODD, Cl3_TPV.
2315: instance Storable Cl3 where
2316:   sizeOf _ = 8 * sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2317:   alignment _ = sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2318:   peek ptr = do
2319:     a0 <- peek (offset 0)
2320:     a1 <- peek (offset 1)
2321:     a2 <- peek (offset 2)
2322:     a3 <- peek (offset 3)
2323:     a23 <- peek (offset 4)
2324:     a31 <- peek (offset 5)
2325:     a12 <- peek (offset 6)
2326:     a123 <- peek (offset 7)
2327:     return $ APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123
2328:       where
2329:         offset i = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double) `plusPtr` (i*8)
2330:   
2331:   poke ptr (toAPS -> APS a0 a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12 a123) = do
2332:     poke (offset 0) a0
2333:     poke (offset 1) a1
2334:     poke (offset 2) a2
2335:     poke (offset 3) a3
2336:     poke (offset 4) a23
2337:     poke (offset 5) a31
2338:     poke (offset 6) a12
2339:     poke (offset 7) a123
2340:       where
2341:         offset i = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double) `plusPtr` (i*8)
2342:   poke _ _ = error "Serious Issues with poke in Cl3.Storable"
2343: 
2344: 
2345: data Cl3_R where
2346:   Cl3_R :: !Double -> Cl3_R
2347: 
2348: toCl3_R :: Cl3 -> Cl3_R
2349: toCl3_R (R a0) = Cl3_R a0
2350: toCl3_R err = error $ "Please don't try and cast something that's not R to Cl3_R, Got: " ++ show err
2351: 
2352: fromCl3_R :: Cl3_R -> Cl3
2353: fromCl3_R (Cl3_R a0) = R a0
2354: 
2355: instance Storable Cl3_R where
2356:   sizeOf _ = sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2357:   alignment _ = sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2358:   peek ptr = do
2359:     a0 <- peek offset
2360:     return $ Cl3_R a0
2361:       where
2362:         offset = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double)
2363: 
2364:   poke ptr (Cl3_R a0) = do
2365:     poke offset a0
2366:       where
2367:         offset = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double)
2368: 
2369: 
2370: data Cl3_V3 where
2371:   Cl3_V3 :: !Double -> !Double -> !Double -> Cl3_V3
2372: 
2373: toCl3_V3 :: Cl3 -> Cl3_V3
2374: toCl3_V3 (V3 a1 a2 a3) = Cl3_V3 a1 a2 a3
2375: toCl3_V3 err = error $ "Please don't try and cast something that's not V3 to Cl3_V3, Got: " ++ show err

2379: 
2380: instance Storable Cl3_V3 where
2381:   sizeOf _ = 3 * sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2382:   alignment _ = sizeOf (undefined :: Double)
2383:   peek ptr = do
2384:     a1 <- peek (offset 0)
2385:     a2 <- peek (offset 1)
2386:     a3 <- peek (offset 2)
2387:     return $ Cl3_V3 a1 a2 a3
2388:       where
2389:         offset i = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double) `plusPtr` (i*8)
2390: 
2391:   poke ptr (Cl3_V3 a1 a2 a3) = do
2392:     poke (offset 0) a1
2393:     poke (offset 1) a2
2394:     poke (offset 2) a3
2395:       where
2396:         offset i = (castPtr ptr :: Ptr Double) `plusPtr` (i*8)

2679: 
2680: 
2681: 
2682: #ifndef O_NO_RANDOM
2683: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2684: -- 
2685: -- Random Instance of Cl3 types with the "System.Random" library.
2686: -- 
2687: --
2688: -- Random helper functions will be based on the "abs x * signum x" decomposition
2689: -- for the single grade elements. The "abs x" will be the random magnitude that
2690: -- is by the default [0,1), and the "signum x" part will be a random direction
2691: -- of a vector or the sign of a scalar. The multi-grade elements will be constructed from
2692: -- a combination of the single grade generators.  Each grade will be evenly
2693: -- distributed across the range.
2694: -- 
2695: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2696: 
2697: -- | 'Random' instance for the 'System.Random' library
2698: instance Random Cl3 where
2699:   randomR (minAbs,maxAbs) g =
2700:     case randomR (fromEnum (minBound :: ConCl3), fromEnum (maxBound :: ConCl3)) g of
2701:       (r, g') -> case toEnum r of
2702:         ConR -> rangeR (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2703:         ConV3 -> rangeV3 (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2704:         ConBV -> rangeBV (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2705:         ConI -> rangeI (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2706:         ConPV -> rangePV (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2707:         ConH -> rangeH (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2708:         ConC -> rangeC (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2709:         ConBPV -> rangeBPV (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2710:         ConODD -> rangeODD (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2711:         ConTPV -> rangeTPV (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2712:         ConAPS -> rangeAPS (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2713:         ConProj -> rangeProjector (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2714:         ConNilpotent -> rangeNilpotent (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2715:         ConUnitary -> rangeUnitary (minAbs,maxAbs) g'
2716: 
2717:   random = randomR (0,1)
2718: 
2719: 
2720: 
2721: -- | 'ConCl3' Bounded Enum Algebraic Data Type of constructors of Cl3
2722: data ConCl3 = ConR
2723:             | ConV3
2724:             | ConBV
2725:             | ConI
2726:             | ConPV
2727:             | ConH
2728:             | ConC
2729:             | ConBPV
2730:             | ConODD
2731:             | ConTPV
2732:             | ConAPS
2733:             | ConProj
2734:             | ConNilpotent
2735:             | ConUnitary
2736:   deriving (Bounded, Enum)
2737: 
2738: 
2739: 
2740: 
2741: -- | 'randR' random Real Scalar (Grade 0) with random magnitude and random sign
2742: randR :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2743: randR = rangeR (0,1)
2744: 
2745: 
2746: -- | 'rangeR' random Real Scalar (Grade 0) with random magnitude within a range and a random sign
2747: rangeR :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2748: rangeR = scalarHelper R
2749: 
2750: 
2751: -- | 'randV3' random Vector (Grade 1) with random magnitude and random direction
2752: -- the direction is using spherical coordinates
2753: randV3 :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2754: randV3 = rangeV3 (0,1)
2755: 
2756: 
2757: -- | 'rangeV3' random Vector (Grade 1) with random magnitude within a range and a random direction
2758: rangeV3 :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2759: rangeV3 = vectorHelper V3
2760: 
2761: 
2762: -- | 'randBV' random Bivector (Grade 2) with random magnitude and random direction
2763: -- the direction is using spherical coordinates
2764: randBV :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2765: randBV = rangeBV (0,1)
2766: 
2767: 
2768: -- | 'rangeBV' random Bivector (Grade 2) with random magnitude in a range and a random direction
2769: rangeBV :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2770: rangeBV = vectorHelper BV
2771: 
2772: 
2773: -- | 'randI' random Imaginary Scalar (Grade 3) with random magnitude and random sign
2774: randI :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2775: randI = rangeI (0,1)
2776: 
2777: 
2778: -- | 'rangeI' random Imaginary Scalar (Grade 3) with random magnitude within a range and random sign
2779: rangeI :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2780: rangeI = scalarHelper I
2781: 
2782: 
2783: -- | 'randPV' random Paravector made from random Grade 0 and Grade 1 elements
2784: randPV :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2785: randPV = rangePV (0,1)
2786: 
2787: 
2788: -- | 'rangePV' random Paravector made from random Grade 0 and Grade 1 elements within a range
2789: rangePV :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2790: rangePV (lo, hi) g =
2791:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2792:       (R a0, g'') = randR g'
2793:       (V3 a1 a2 a3, g''') = randV3 g''
2794:       sumsqs = a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2
2795:       x = abs a0 * sqrt sumsqs
2796:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ a0^2 + sumsqs + x + x
2797:       mag = scale * invMag
2798:   in (PV (mag * a0) (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3), g''')
2799: 
2800: 
2801: -- | 'randH' random Quaternion made from random Grade 0 and Grade 2 elements
2802: randH :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2803: randH = rangeH (0,1)
2804: 
2805: 
2806: -- | 'rangeH' random Quaternion made from random Grade 0 and Grade 2 elements within a range
2807: rangeH :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2808: rangeH (lo, hi) g =
2809:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2810:       (R a0, g'') = randR g'
2811:       (BV a23 a31 a12, g''') = randBV g''
2812:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ a0^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2
2813:       mag = scale * invMag
2814:   in (H (mag * a0) (mag * a23) (mag * a31) (mag * a12), g''')
2815: 
2816: 
2817: -- | 'randC' random combination of Grade 0 and Grade 3
2818: randC :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2819: randC = rangeC (0,1)
2820: 
2821: 
2822: -- | 'rangeC' random combination of Grade 0 and Grade 3 within a range
2823: rangeC :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2824: rangeC (lo, hi) g =
2825:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2826:       (phi, g'') = randomR (0, 2*pi) g'
2827:   in (C (scale * cos phi) (scale * sin phi), g'')
2828: 
2829: 
2830: -- | 'randBPV' random combination of Grade 1 and Grade 2
2831: randBPV :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2832: randBPV = rangeBPV (0,1)
2833: 
2834: 
2835: -- | 'rangeBPV' random combination of Grade 1 and Grade 2 within a range
2836: rangeBPV :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2837: rangeBPV (lo, hi) g =
2838:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2839:       (V3 a1 a2 a3, g'') = randV3 g'
2840:       (BV a23 a31 a12, g''') = randBV g''
2841:       x = sqrt $ (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2 + (a1*a12 - a3*a23)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2
2842:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ a1^2 + a23^2 + a2^2 + a31^2 + a3^2 + a12^2 + x + x
2843:       mag = scale * invMag
2844:   in (BPV (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3) (mag * a23) (mag * a31) (mag * a12), g''')
2845: 
2846: 
2847: -- | 'randODD' random combination of Grade 1 and Grade 3
2848: randODD :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2849: randODD = rangeODD (0,1)
2850: 
2851: 
2852: -- | 'rangeODD' random combination of Grade 1 and Grade 3 within a range
2853: rangeODD :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2854: rangeODD (lo, hi) g =
2855:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2856:       (V3 a1 a2 a3, g'') = randV3 g'
2857:       (I a123, g''') = randI g''
2858:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a123^2
2859:       mag = scale * invMag
2860:   in (ODD (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3) (mag * a123), g''')
2861: 
2862: 
2863: -- | 'randTPV' random combination of Grade 2 and Grade 3
2864: randTPV :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2865: randTPV = rangeTPV (0,1)
2866: 
2867: 
2868: -- | 'rangeTPV' random combination of Grade 2 and Grade 3 within a range
2869: rangeTPV :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2870: rangeTPV (lo, hi) g =
2871:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2872:       (BV a23 a31 a12, g'') = randBV g'
2873:       (I a123, g''') = randI g''
2874:       sumsqs = a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2
2875:       x = abs a123 * sqrt sumsqs
2876:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ sumsqs + a123^2 + x + x
2877:       mag = scale * invMag
2878:   in (TPV (mag * a23) (mag * a31) (mag * a12) (mag * a123), g''')
2879: 
2880: 
2881: -- | 'randAPS' random combination of all 4 grades
2882: randAPS :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2883: randAPS = rangeAPS (0,1)
2884: 
2885: 
2886: -- | 'rangeAPS' random combination of all 4 grades within a range
2887: rangeAPS :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2888: rangeAPS (lo, hi) g =
2889:   let (R scale, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2890:       (C a0 a123, g'') = randC g'
2891:       (V3 a1 a2 a3, g''') = randV3 g''
2892:       (BV a23 a31 a12, g'v) = randBV g'''
2893:       x = sqrt $ (a0*a1 + a123*a23)^2 + (a0*a2 + a123*a31)^2 + (a0*a3 + a123*a12)^2 + (a2*a12 - a3*a31)^2 + (a3*a23 - a1*a12)^2 + (a1*a31 - a2*a23)^2
2894:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ a0^2 + a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + a23^2 + a31^2 + a12^2 + a123^2 + x + x
2895:       mag = scale * invMag
2896:   in (APS (mag * a0) (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3) (mag * a23) (mag * a31) (mag * a12) (mag * a123), g'v)
2897: 
2898: 
2899: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2900: -- Additional Random generators
2901: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2902: -- | 'randUnitV3' a unit vector with a random direction
2903: randUnitV3 :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2904: randUnitV3 g =
2905:   let (theta, g') = randomR (0,2*pi) g
2906:       (u, g'') = randomR (-1,1) g'
2907:       semicircle = sqrt (1-u^2)
2908:   in (V3 (semicircle * cos theta) (semicircle * sin theta) u, g'')
2909: 
2910: 
2911: -- | 'randProjector' a projector with a random direction
2912: randProjector :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2913: randProjector g =
2914:   let (V3 a1 a2 a3, g') = randUnitV3 g
2915:   in (PV 0.5 (0.5 * a1) (0.5 * a2) (0.5 * a3), g')
2916: 
2917: 
2918: -- | 'rangeProjector' a projector with a range of random magnitudes and directions
2919: rangeProjector :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2920: rangeProjector (lo, hi) g =
2921:   let (R mag, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2922:       (PV a0 a1 a2 a3, g'') = randProjector g'
2923:   in (PV (mag * a0) (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3), g'')
2924: 
2925: 
2926: -- | 'randNilpotent' a nilpotent element with a random orientation
2927: randNilpotent :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2928: randNilpotent g =
2929:   let (PV a0 a1 a2 a3, g') = randProjector g
2930:       (V3 b1 b2 b3, g'') = randUnitV3 g'
2931:       c1 = a2*b3 - a3*b2
2932:       c2 = a3*b1 - a1*b3
2933:       c3 = a1*b2 - a2*b1 -- (V3 c1 c2 c3) vector normal to the projector: mIx.toBV $ toV3 p * v
2934:       invMag = recip.sqrt $ c1^2 + c2^2 + c3^2
2935:       d1 = invMag * c1
2936:       d2 = invMag * c2
2937:       d3 = invMag * c3  -- (V3 d1 d2 d3) unit vector normal to the projector
2938:   in (BPV (d1*a0) (d2*a0) (d3*a0) (d2*a3 - d3*a2) (d3*a1 - d1*a3) (d1*a2 - d2*a1), g'')
2939: 
2940: 
2941: -- | 'rangeNilpotent' a nilpotent with a range of random magnitudes and orientations
2942: rangeNilpotent :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2943: rangeNilpotent (lo, hi)  g =
2944:   let (R mag, g') = rangeR (lo, hi) g
2945:       (BPV a1 a2 a3 a23 a31 a12, g'') = randNilpotent g'
2946:   in (BPV (mag * a1) (mag * a2) (mag * a3) (mag * a23) (mag * a31) (mag * a12), g'')
2947: 
2948: 
2949: -- | 'randUnitary' a unitary element with a random orientation
2950: randUnitary :: RandomGen g => g -> (Cl3, g)
2951: randUnitary g =
2952:   let (tpv,g') = randTPV g
2953:   in (exp tpv,g')
2954: 
2955: 
2956: -- | 'rangeUnitary' a unitary element with a range of random magnitudes and orientations, the exponential of a triparavector
2957: rangeUnitary :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2958: rangeUnitary (lo, hi) g =
2959:   let (tpv, g') = rangeTPV (lo, hi) g
2960:   in (exp tpv, g')
2961: 
2962: 
2963: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2964: -- helper functions
2965: -------------------------------------------------------------------
2966: magHelper :: RandomGen g => (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Double, g)
2967: magHelper (lo, hi) g =
2968:   let R lo' = abs lo
2969:       R hi' = abs hi
2970:   in randomR (lo', hi') g
2971: 
2972: 
2973: scalarHelper :: RandomGen g => (Double -> Cl3) -> (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2974: scalarHelper con rng g =
2975:   let (mag, g') = magHelper rng g
2976:       (sign, g'') = random g'
2977:   in if sign
2978:      then (con mag, g'')
2979:      else (con (negate mag), g'')
2980: 
2981: 
2982: vectorHelper :: RandomGen g => (Double -> Double -> Double -> Cl3) -> (Cl3, Cl3) -> g -> (Cl3, g)
2983: vectorHelper con rng g =
2984:   let (mag, g') = magHelper rng g
2985:       (V3 x y z, g'') = randUnitV3 g'
2986:   in (con (mag * x) (mag * y) (mag * z), g'')
2987: 
2988: 
2989: #endif
2990: 
2991: -- End of File
